      <hedline>
        <hl1>Desperate Passage</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas Curley letter on Michael Finkel's June 18 article holds village elders in Ile de la Tortue had little regard for welfare of Haitian boat refugees</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Your article makes clear the basic human inclination to migrate from bad to better circumstances. Sadly, it is also a basic human instinct to profit from migration. The village elders in le de la Tortue, Haiti, had little concern for the welfare of the passengers.</p>
        <p>Thomas Curley  Montreal</p>
      </block>
